## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q1 — Rate Limiting Strategy**: How aggressive should scraping be? I recommend a **2-second delay between HTTP requests** per provider, with a configurable `SCRAPE_DELAY_SECONDS` env var. Too fast risks IP bans from coupon sites. **Please confirm or specify.**

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q2 — Language Detection Library**: For English-only filtering, I recommend using Python's `langdetect` library on course titles/descriptions. As a secondary signal, the scraper checks if the source page explicitly lists the language. **Please confirm or suggest an alternative.**

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q3 — Coupon Validation Depth**: Should the scraper perform a HEAD request to each coupon/Udemy URL to verify it's still live during scraping? This adds reliability but doubles scrape time. I recommend **yes for the initial scrape, skip on subsequent scheduled runs if the course was verified < 6 hours ago**. **Please confirm.**

