#### [NEW] [src/queue.py](file:///home/akai/Desktop/Udemy%20Course%20Finder/scraper/src/queue.py)
- Implements BullMQ-compatible job consumption from Redis
- BullMQ stores jobs in Redis as sorted sets/lists under `bull:<queue-name>:wait`, `bull:<queue-name>:active`, etc.
- The Python consumer uses `BRPOPLPUSH` (or `BLMOVE`) pattern to atomically dequeue jobs
- Supports job types: `scrape-single` (one provider), `scrape-all` (all enabled providers), `test-provider` (connectivity check)
- Reports job completion/failure back to Redis for the NestJS backend to read

