#### [NEW] 9 Provider Scrapers

Each provider scraper (`real_discount.py` through `course_vania.py`):
- Extends `BaseScraper`
- Implements `scrape()` to:
  1. Fetch listing pages (with pagination where applicable)
  2. Parse course cards/links from HTML using BeautifulSoup
  3. Optionally fetch individual course detail pages for missing data
  4. Extract: title, Udemy URL, coupon URL, category, thumbnail, rating, instructor
  5. Extract Udemy course ID from URL patterns using `url_parser.py`
  6. Return `list[ScrapedCourse]`

| # | Provider | Scraping Strategy |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | **Real Discount** | JSON API endpoint (`/api/...`); paginated; rich data including rating, instructor, category |
| 2 | **Courson** | HTML scrape of listing pages; course cards with title + coupon link |
| 3 | **Tutorial Bar** | HTML scrape; paginated archive pages; each post links to Udemy coupon |
| 4 | **E-next** | HTML scrape; grid listing with category tags |
| 5 | **iDownloadCoupons** | HTML scrape; listing page + detail pages for full coupon URL |
| 6 | **DiscUdemy** | Multi-step: listing → detail page → reveal actual Udemy coupon URL |
| 7 | **Udemy Freebies** | HTML scrape; listing with direct coupon links |
| 8 | **Course Joiner** | HTML scrape; similar to Tutorial Bar pattern |
| 9 | **Course Vania** | HTML scrape; listing + detail pages; may use JavaScript redirect |

#### [NEW] Pipeline Stages

##### [src/pipeline/normalizer.py](file:///home/akai/Desktop/Udemy%20Course%20Finder/scraper/src/pipeline/normalizer.py)
- Normalize titles (strip excess whitespace, fix encoding, remove "[FREE]" prefixes)
- Normalize URLs (strip tracking params, resolve redirects to clean Udemy URL)
- Map source-specific category strings to the seeded category slugs (fuzzy match)
- Extract Udemy course ID from URL using `url_parser.py`

##### [src/pipeline/validator.py](file:///home/akai/Desktop/Udemy%20Course%20Finder/scraper/src/pipeline/validator.py)
- Required fields: `title`, `udemy_url` or `coupon_url` (at least one must be present)
- URL format validation (must be valid HTTP/HTTPS URL)
- Optional: HEAD request to coupon URL to verify it resolves (configurable via `VALIDATE_URLS` env var)

##### [src/pipeline/language_filter.py](file:///home/akai/Desktop/Udemy%20Course%20Finder/scraper/src/pipeline/language_filter.py)
- If `language` field is explicitly set by the scraper → use it directly
- Otherwise, run `langdetect.detect()` on `title + description`
- Only pass courses where detected language is `en` (English)
- Log rejected courses with reason

##### [src/pipeline/deduplicator.py](file:///home/akai/Desktop/Udemy%20Course%20Finder/scraper/src/pipeline/deduplicator.py)
- **Primary key**: `udemy_course_id` — if two courses from different providers have the same Udemy course ID, keep the one with richer metadata (more fields populated)
- **Fallback**: Normalized title matching (case-insensitive, stripped of special chars) when `udemy_course_id` is unavailable
- Within a single batch: dedup before storing
- Cross-batch: check against existing DB records — update `last_verified_at` if the course already exists, insert if new

##### [src/pipeline/store.py](file:///home/akai/Desktop/Udemy%20Course%20Finder/scraper/src/pipeline/store.py)
- Upsert courses to PostgreSQL using `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT` on the `unique_course_per_provider` constraint
- On conflict: update `last_verified_at`, `coupon_url` (may change), `is_active = true`
- Create a `logs` entry recording: provider_id, job_id, status, courses_found/accepted/rejected, timing
- Update `providers` table: `last_run_at`, `last_status`

